  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Graphics Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate in conceptualizing and designing projects to meet client and supervisor expectations</li><li>Develop designs, concepts, and sample layouts applying layout principles and aesthetic design concepts to enhance visual communication</li><li>Determine size and arrangement of illustrative materials and copy, selecting appropriate style and size of type to optimize design impact</li><li>Review final layouts and recommend improvements to ensure quality and effectiveness</li><li>Prepare illustrations or rough sketches, engage with clients or supervisors for feedback, and implement necessary revisions</li><li>Utilize computer software to generate new images that align with project requirements and creative direction</li><li>Manage workload independently and deliver high-quality designs within tight deadlines in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Demonstrate initiative and collaborate effectively within a team to support project goals</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or Diploma in Graphic or Visual Communications Design</li><li>Proficiency in Adobe Illustrator, Photoshop, and InDesign software in a PC environment</li><li>Strong IT skills to efficiently operate design software and tools</li><li>Meticulous attention to detail in artwork and layout execution</li><li>Positive attitude and resilience to work under pressure while maintaining quality standards</li><li>Ability to work autonomously and contribute proactively in a dynamic team setting</li></ul>",
